1.definition: Verb. To start to do something. For example, lets begin playing Pictoword!

2.definition: Noun. The act of taking someone's outstretched hand in your own and shaking it, as a greeting or farewell.

3.definition: Noun. A tasty food consisting of various ingredients between two pieces of bread.

4.definition: Noun. Colored makeup that is applied to the lips. Comes in a wide variety of colors, mostly shades of red.

5.definition: Noun. A delicious food with meat on a stick, usually red and hot.

6.definition: Noun. A ship that travels under water rather than on the surface of it, often noisy and cramped.

7.definition: Noun. A container with a handle used to store clothing and souvenirs when traveling.

8.definition: Noun. The cost of a ticket to fly somewhere, usually more expensive than you were expecting.

9.definition: Noun. The most important member of an organization, often takes part in illegal activity.

10.definition: Noun. A rope that you swing over your head and under your feet as you jump, either for fun or as a workout.

11.definition: Noun. A thin wooden tool with a lead core that allows you to write and draw on paper.

12.definition: Noun. A device used to remove corks from bottle necks, often for wine bottles.

13.definition: Noun. A piece of jewelry worn on the ear that typically comes in pairs, losing one of these can be pretty annoying.

14.definition: Noun. A set of letters arranged in a particular order, used for writing a language.

15.definition: Noun. A picture glued to cardboard and cut into various shapes. Assembling the pieces correctly shows the picture.

16.definition: Noun. A game played between two teams of eleven people where the goal is to get the ball to either end of the field.

17.definition: Verb. The act of ending a worker's employment without the worker having done anything wrong.

18.definition: Noun. A cloth pouch filled with beans. Depending on size, can be used as a toy or as a comfortable seat.

19.definition: Noun. A large amount of information stored on a computer system in an easy-to-search way.

20.definition: Noun. An opening in a city street often covered with a large, round metal lid. Usually leads to sewers.

21.definition: Noun. A sea creature with a soft body and stinging tentacles. The tops don't sting you! Awful with peanut butter.

22.definition: Verb. To destroy something by forcibly twisting and tearing it to the point that it cannot be restored.

23.definition: Noun. A delicious food with meat on a stick, covered in cornmeal batter and deep fried. Tasty with mustard.

24.definition: Noun. A computer system that allows users to access electronic mail messages from any computer. Often has junk mail.

25.definition: Noun. The space that a pilot sits in when flying a plane.

26.definition: Noun. A transportation system which uses special vehicles that travel on roads of metal rails.

27.definition: Noun. A woven material used for covering floors. Juice stains can be difficult to remove from it.

28.definition: Noun. A liquid temporarily used to clean the mouth, freshen the breath, and improve one's luck. Not a substitute for brushing teeth.

29.definition: Noun. A children's plaything that consists of a board with a heightened central pivot, allowing one end to lower as the other lifts up.

30.definition: Noun. A light net worn over the head to keep hair in place. Often used by lunchlords and lunchladies.

31.definition: Noun. A small spoon used to put sugar in coffee and tea. Debate continues over whether milk is added before or after sugar.

32.definition: Noun. An amount equal to 1,000,000. Also used informally to say "a whole lot", such as "I have a million things to do today."

33.definition: Noun. An informal meal in which each guest brings a dish that is then shared with the other guests. A tasty way to build friendship.

34.definition: Noun. A multicolored arch that sometimes appears in the sky when it rains on a sunny day. Considered a sign of good luck.

35.definition: Noun. A small brown mammal whose back has a coat of short firmly-attached spines. They won't poke you if you give them space.

36.definition: Noun. In the United States, a coin worth 1/100th of a dollar, also called a 'cent'. Virtually worthless, but they can be saved up.

37.definition: Noun. A wide key found on computer and typewriter keyboards that is used to create space between words.

38.definition: Noun. The plural of person. They're everywhere - there's even one hiding in your mirror.

39.definition: Noun. A phone that operates wirelessly to make and receive calls, send text messages, and look at memes on the Internet.

40.definition: Noun. A computer that is small enough to carry around and folds flat for storage. Seems to attract spilled coffee and tea.

41.definition: Verb. To walk across a street at a point where you are not allowed to cross. A crime where the perpetrator is often also the victim.

42.definition: Noun. A drink made of milk, ice cream, and fruit, chocolate, or some other flavoring, mixed in a machine. As tasty as it is unhealthy.

43.definition: Noun. A small hand-held telescope that allows for the viewing of distant objects. Often employed by pirates and explorers in movies.

44.definition: Noun. Another way to refer to a refrigerator. Based on the fact that old fridges were just boxes with ice compartments.

45.definition: Noun. A round glass container with a filament that glows brightly with electricity. Also used as a symbol of inspiration.

46.definition: Noun. A very frightening and unpleasant dream, or an event that you wish was just a dream.

47.definition: Noun. A decorative object consisting of a clear glass or plastic globe that contains a clear liquid with floating particles of fake snow.

48.definition: Noun. A system of connected parts that encourages movement or communication between the various parts.

49.definition: Noun. A container for making and serving tea. Famously features a handle and a spout.

50.definition: Noun. The space in a wall where a door opens, through which you can access a room or building. Not suitable earthquake protection.

51.definition: Noun. To act in a way or say something that is offensive or rude to someone. Not everyone agrees about what is or isn't insulting.

52.definition: Noun. A watch that you can start and stop to measure the passage of time. A runner's best friend and partner in performance.

53.definition: Noun. A small golden fish often kept as a pet. Sometimes won at carnivals, usually flushed down toilets, rarely found on skateboards.

54.definition: Noun. Dirty cloth goods, such as clothing, bed sheets, etc., that have been or need to be washed.

55.definition: Noun. An adult male horse, particularly one that is prized for its heritage.

56.definition: Noun. A small book of checks in which you can write information for making payments or bank withdrawals. Easy to misplace.

57.definition: Noun. A disagreement between people or organizations that is brought to a court of law for a decision.

58.definition: Noun. A piece of jewelry worn around the neck, such as a chain or a string of decorative stones or beads.

59.definition: Noun. Goods carried by a ship, aircraft, or other vehicle.

60.definition: Noun. A game where cards are played onto the table until a Jack appears, at which point everyone tries to slap the stack of cards.

61.definition: Noun. Slang for someone younger than the age of consent, with the implication that a person above the age of consent might find them attractive.

62.definition: Noun. A small nut that grows in a shell underground. Greatly enhanced by a little bit of salt. Championed by George W. Carver.

63.definition: Noun. The round bone at the front of the knee joint. Not exactly a small hat for your knee - though in a way, it is.

64.definition: Adjective. Used to describe something that takes place for or during the night.

65.definition: Noun. The day of the week after Thursday but before Saturday. The gateway to the weekend.

66.definition: Noun. The style in which someone's hair is cut, or the occasion of getting one's hair cut and styled. Surprisingly pricey for good ones.

67.definition: Noun. A plastic or wooden object used to fasten clothes to a clothesline while they dry. There never seems to be enough.

68.definition: Noun. A sweet frozen food made of milk, cream, sugar, and various flavorings. Best on hot summer days.

69.definition: Noun. A small device used for catching mice by tempting them with cheese or peanut butter. Typically not very humane.

70.definition: Noun. A mark left on a surface by a foot. Also used to measure the size and effect of something - such as "carbon footprint".

71.definition: Noun. A list of the employees of a company, showing how much (or little) each one earns.

72.definition: Noun. A formal outfit consisting of a black jacket and black pants, often worn with a bow tie. Favored by secret agents and Sailor Earth.

73.definition: Noun. A piece of flavored hard candy shaped like a curved cane, and often peppermint flavored. Supports very little weight.

74.definition: Adjective. Used to describe something fast and direct, such as an express bus or express shipping.

75.definition: Noun. A fairly common eye infection that results in red eyes and swollen eyelids. Pretty contagious, so be sure to wash your hands.

76.definition: Noun. A mother or father of another person, animal, or company.

77.definition: Noun. An unpleasant but harmless burning feeling in the chest caused by indigestion. Can be calmed with antacids.

78.definition: Adjective. The feeling of being in love or missing a loved one to the point that you're unable to act normally. Common in teenagers.

79.definition: Noun. An infield baseball player position between second and third base. Easy to blame for making mistakes under pressure.

80.definition: Noun. A set of keys arranged in rows used to type on a computer, also used to refer to piano-like musical devices.

81.definition: Noun. An industrial vehicle with two metal prongs in the front, used to lift and move heavy goods.

82.definition: Noun. A building with a roof and walls made of a transparent material meant to help plants inside of it grow.

83.definition: Noun. Behavior that is slightly bad and causes minor trouble, but is not intended to cause serious harm to anyone.

84.definition: Noun. A sweet bread food made from cornmeal. Excellent with stews, chowders, and chili.

85.definition: Noun. A light-grey rock formed from coral minerals, typically used as a building material and as a component in cement.

86.definition: Adjective. Showing or expressing thankfulness, particularly to another person. We're grateful you're playing Pictoword!

87.definition: Noun. An annual American football game played between the top two teams of that year, to determine the king of US football.

88.definition: Noun. A group of people who travel together to work or school in the same vehicle in order to save on tolls and gas money.

89.definition: Noun. A book of paper for writing on. Often used to contain notes, secrets, jokes, doodles, recipes, and flattened plants.

90.definition: Noun. A reaction to a process or activity, as well as the information from such a reaction.

91.definition: Noun. A winged vehicle with engines that permit it to fly. A miracle of modern engineering, and statistically safer than a car.

92.definition: Noun. A small round red beetle with black spots, sometimes called a ladybird. Harmless unless you're a leaf.

93.definition: Noun. A period of great success, popularity, or power. Hard to see as it is happening, easy to see in hindsight.

94.definition: Noun. A vehicle used for travel in space. Examples include the Millenium Falcon, the Enterprise, and Firefly.

95.definition: Noun. Either of a pair of small organs in the body which remove waste from the blood and produce urine. One is enough, two is better.

96.definition: Noun. A man whose job it is to bring milk to your home in the early morning. An endangered species.

97.definition: Noun. A person whose job is cutting and styling hair, particular of men and boys. In the past, they also worked as surgeons and dentists.

98.definition: Noun. A small round iced cake, usually meant for one person. These can range from modest to surprisingly elaborate.

99.definition: Noun. A U-shaped metal object attached to the bottom of a horse's hoof meant to protect it from unnecessary wear and tear.

100.definition: Verb. To make something whiter or to become whiter.

101.definition: Noun. The largest prize offered in a competition, often one that is incremented and added to until it is won.

102.definition: Noun. Historically, a member of a low social class of farm workers. Informally, someone who is unpleasant and does not behave well.

103.definition: Noun. A tall plant featuring a large, round yellow flower. The seeds are tasty with a bit of salt, and they can be pressed to make oil.

104.definition: Verb. To be unable, or not allowed, to do a particular thing.

105.definition: Noun. A climbing plant that has white or yellow flowers, depending on the season.

106.definition: Noun. A bag worn on the back with shoulder straps and various pockets that can be useful to carry things.

107.definition: Noun. In which a mass of rock and dirt slips and falls down a steep slope. Can also refer to a decisive victory in an election.

108.definition: Noun. A cone-shaped electric voice-amplifying device, often heard at political rallies, public demonstrations, and cheering sections.

109.definition: Noun. A tall grassy plant with hard hollow stems. The primary staple of a panda's diet.

110.definition: Noun. A miniature toy house used for playing with dolls.

111.definition: Noun. A room or building where people work, or where you can get a particular service, as in "post office". A cage for humans.

113.definition: Noun. A large tropical fruit with a hard, hairy brown shell and firm, white, edible flesh. Not actually a nut!

114.definition: Noun. A plant that is used to produce a strong, fresh, sweet flavoring. Great in certain drinks.

115.definition: Noun. A piece of land on which grapevines are grown and cultivated, often for the purposes of making wine. Usually a good tourist spot.

116.definition: Noun. The color that is a mix of red and yellow. Also, a round citrus fruit of that same color.

117.definition: Noun. A thick, slowly-cooked stew consisting of okra, vegetables, meat, and fish. The official state cuisine of Louisiana, USA.

118.definition: Noun. A family of winged beetles that are known for their ability to create their own light in order to attract mates. Also known as lightning bugs.

119.definition: Noun. The shape of objects against the sky, particularly the silhouette produced by the buildings of a city.

120.definition: Preposition. Describes a position in or to the back of something. Also used to describe responsibility - "Who is behind this?" Polite way to refer to a butt.

121.definition: Noun. A piece of fabric or paper used to cover a table for decoration as well as protection. A useful component in some magic tricks.

122.definition: Verb. To synchronize lip movements to pre-recorded audio, often to give the illusion of live performance.

123.definition: Noun. A thick informal shirt, often made of cotton, that is worn for exercise or to stay warm. Oversized ones are especially comfy.

124.definition: Noun. Something that is particularly easy to accomplish, such as writing one's name on a test or walking on cakes.

125.definition: Noun. The flat part of the face, above the eyes and below the hairline. Particularly large ones are humorously referred to as 'fiveheads'.

126.definition: Noun. A small structure built and located among the branches of a tree. Sometimes used by children as secret club hideouts.

127.definition: Noun. A thick, soft food made of oats and grains boiled in water or milk. You probably already know this as oatmeal. Consider adding honey.

128.definition: Noun. A written agreement between two or more countries that is formally approved and signed by their leaders. Meant to be binding, often fluid.

129.definition: Noun. A place where aircraft regularly take off and land, with buildings for passenger and flight management. Often a pain to drive to.

130.definition: Noun. A commonly-seen small gray-brown bird, though some people use the term to denote any small sparrow-like bird.

131.definition: Noun. The hard seed pod that pine trees drop. Each individual 'scale' protects a pine seed, so one pinecone can result in dozens of trees.

132.definition: Noun. Someone, usually a romantic partner, with whom you have a special relationship with, and who you know and love deeply. A kindred spirit.

133.definition: Noun. A thin flap of tissue in your ear that allows you to hear. Mechanically similar to a tiny microphone, very useful for enjoying music.

134.definition: Noun. A small fish that swims vertically and has a horse-like head and a curly tail. Male seahorses give birth, rather than the females.

135.definition: Noun. A vertical pipe on a street or building that firefighters can get water from to put out fires. Don't hit one with your car or you'll have a bad time.

136.definition: Verb. To breathe air, smoke, or gas into your lungs. It's not advisable to inhale other things, such as water or chili.

137.definition: Noun. The ability to protect from attack or harm, or something used or done to grant that ability. A good one is the best offense.

138.definition: Verb. To track or move along a particular way after someone or something has already done so, or to move along a particular path.

139.definition: Noun. A set of clothes worn in order to give off a particular appearance, typically an unusual one, often for amusement or entertainment.

140.definition: Noun. A portable electronic sound system with a radio, cassette deck, or CD player, capable of producing powerfully amplified sound.

141.definition: Noun. A boat that uses steam power to move. Somewhat old-fashioned, they dramatically improved trade and shipping in the 1800s.

142.definition: Noun. A group of people brought together to take part in an event or team. Examples include a concert lineup, a soccer lineup, and a police lineup.

143.definition: Noun. A young cat. Typically max-level cuteness magi, kittens are dangerously adorable and can lead to unexpected cuddles and snoot boops.

144.definition: Noun. An opening in the wall of a building or vehicle, typically covered with glass, that lets light and air in and allows people inside to see out.

145.definition: Adjective. Against the law. Not legal. Something that shouldn't be done.

146.definition: Noun. A game in which players try to guess a word by guessing the individual letters. Players have a limited number of guesses before they lose.

147.definition: Noun. A long pointed stick of ice that hangs down from something, formed when dripping water freezes. Satisfying to break.

148.definition: Noun. One of the four parts a year is divided into, winter, spring, summer, fall. Certain parts of the world have fewer, such as "hot" and "less hot".

149.definition: Noun. A social gathering at which people eat, drink, and generally have a nice time. Can be used to note a group of people - e.g. 'party of four'.

150.definition: Noun. A child's toy consisting of a stick with brightly colored pieces of plastic at one end, which are able to turn freely in the wind.

151.definition: Noun. A person who sails on the sea and attacks and steals from other ships. Portrayed in movies as incredibly charming.

152.definition: Noun. Historically, armor made of thin metal plates that was developed as an improvement upon chainmail armor.

153.definition: Noun. The current day. As an adverb, used to note something done on this day. Comes after yesterday, but before tomorrow.

154.definition: Noun. An agreement between two people or groups in which each side commits to doing something in exchange for something else. Also, a deal.

155.definition: Noun. A small juicy red fruit shaped like a rounded cone with a leafy top and tiny edible seeds on the outside. Great with whipped cream.

156.definition: Noun. A large juicy fruit known to grow in hot tropical regions. Has rough skin with a pointed leafy top. A symbol of hospitality and greeting.

157.definition: Noun. A piece of furniture with shelves or drawers that can be used for storing and displaying things.

158.definition: Noun. An action or event that is considered immoral, resulting in a public reaction of shock or anger.

159.definition: Noun. A person who is studying at a school, or someone who is particularly interested in a given subject.

160.definition: Noun. Work done or help provided by a person or organization for others or the public at large.

161.definition: Noun. A famous and successful performer of music, or a person who is treated with the admiration that such a performer receives.

162.definition: Noun. A piece of land completely surrounded by water.

163.definition: Noun. A meal eaten in the morning, as the first meal of the day - at least, it should be. A great deal of effort is put into keeping them balanced.

164.definition: Noun. A place where something exciting is likely to take place. In terms of modern technology, a public wireless Internet access point.

165.definition: Noun. A person who flies an aircraft or directs a ship through water.

166.definition: Noun. An informal term for a detective, possibly originating from the shoes worn by them that allowed them to move in stealth.

167.definition: Noun. An important event in the development or history of something or in someone's life.

168.definition: Noun. The best, most important, or most interesting part of something.

169.definition: Noun. A small electric light that can be carried and aimed with one hand.

170.definition: Verb. To steal things of little value, or in small amounts. Typically used in reference to petty theft.

171.definition: Noun. A place where a road and a railroad intersect, a marked place where a road can be crossed safely, or a journey across a body of water.

172.definition: Noun. Water moving in a powerful circular current, sucking in anything that floats near it.

173.definition: Noun. A beam of light that comes from the moon.

174.definition: Noun. A small sea creature with a shell that tightly attaches itself in large numbers to rocks and the bottoms of boats. Difficult to remove.

175.definition: Noun. Any of a group of mammals that typically have flat faces and long tails, especially the smaller members of this group.

176.definition: Noun. A fast acrobatic movement in which a person tumbles sideways along their hands and feet like a rolling wheel.

177.definition: Noun. A piece of material worn around the wrist, often to hold a watch. Sometimes given at concerts and events as proof of entry.

178.definition: Noun. An obstruction or obstacle, anything used or acting to block someone from going somewhere or doing something.

179.definition: Noun. Crushed, milled oats, especially when boiled in water or milk into a breakfast porridge.

180.definition: Noun. A beverage made with lemon juice, sugar, and water. Can be purchased from children for pocket change.

181.definition: Noun. A person who works at a hotel and performs tasks for guests, such as carrying luggage and opening doors

182.definition: Verb. To damage, weaken, or perturb something, making it less effective.

183.definition: Noun. A string, ring, or tube of pasta or a similar dough, typically made with egg and served with a sauce or in a soup.

184.definition: Noun. A shelf that holds books. Sort of self explanatory. A storage unit for thousands of hours of escapism.

185.definition: Adjective. Showing a lack of care about risks, danger, or the consequences of one's actions. Being a 'loose cannon'.

186.definition: Noun. Someone who uses skill and deception to win at card games, often in order to make a great deal of money. Also known as a 'card sharp'.

187.definition: Noun. A drink that is a mixture of two or more other drinks. Also used more generally for mixtures of things. Also used to describe a shrimp dish.

188.definition: Noun. The responsibility of reporting or writing about a particular subject in the media. Also, the state of being protected from loss via insurance.

189.definition: Noun. An area of flat ground outdoors that is partially or completely surrounded by buildings.

190.definition: Noun. A shorthair breed of dog known for being particularly strong. Often assumed to be inherently aggressive.

191.definition: Noun. A chemical element that is found in all living creatures, coal, and oil. In its purest state, carbon forms graphite as well as diamonds.

192.definition: Noun. Goods transported together, or the act of transporting them.

193.definition: Noun. A wax structure made by bees to store honey. Some people like to eat chunks of the comb, but most prefer the honey alone.

194.definition: Noun. A type of flying insect with four large, typically colorful wings. Their eyes have six-thousand lenses and can see UV light patterns.

195.definition: Noun. An oval vegetable with a shiny, dark purple skin. Excellent when oven-roasted.

196.definition: Adjective. Worried, unhappy, or angry. When referring to a stomach, it means ill or unwell.

197.definition: Noun. A neck injury caused by a sudden back-and-forth head movement, often as a result of a car accident.

198.definition: Noun. A list of things you want, and often things you know that you cannot have due to price or rarity.

199.definition: Noun. A men's hairstyle in which the hair is cut very short.

200.definition: Noun. A musical instrument played by blowing air into a bag and squeezing the bag to force the air out of its pipes.

201.definition: Noun. A conceptual area of interest, or a literal area over which someone has control.

202.definition: Noun. A cozier way of saying sleep.

203.definition: Adjective. Of or describing someone or something who is famous and admired, especially due to a particular talent.

204.definition: Noun. A dark brown, bitter drink that is served hot, typically enjoyed in the mornings or after meals. A good source of caffeine for programmers.

205.definition: Noun. A downward movement generated solely by the force of gravity.

206.definition: Verb. To stop using a computer system or program, often through a particular command.

207.definition: Noun. A small furry animal with a short stubby tail, often kept as a pet. Formerly known for their fondness of dancing.
